MASCOT 1: CHASE (BASE EDITION)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

MYTHOLOGY BASIS: Inspired by pursuit/chase myths (Atalanta, fleet-footed heroes)
PERSONALITY: Energetic, minimalist, efficient, encouraging
TARGET USERS: New Linux users, hardware recyclers, minimalists

VISUAL DESIGN:
• Species: Anthropomorphic cheetah or swift fox
• Color Palette: Light blues, whites, silver accents (minimalist theme)
• Key Features: Streamlined design, athletic build, friendly expression
• Accessories: Simple digital wristband, lightweight running shoes
• Pose Options: Running stance, welcoming gesture, pointing forward

CHARACTER TRAITS:
• Enthusiastic about speed and efficiency
• Helps users understand minimal resource usage
• Encourages exploration with limited tools
• Positive attitude about "doing more with less"

TECHNICAL SPECIFICATIONS:
• Primary sprite: 256x256px, PNG with transparency
• Boot screen variant: 400x300px, optimized palette
• Icon variants: 64x64px, 32x32px, 16x16px
• Animation frames (optional): 4-frame idle loop
• Storage budget: <300KB total for all variants

DIALOGUE EXAMPLES:
"Let's see how fast we can make your system run!"
"Who needs bloat when you've got speed?"
"Your hardware may be old, but together we'll make it shine!"

