CROSS-MASCOT DESIGN REQUIREMENTS
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

CONSISTENCY STANDARDS:
• All mascots share similar art style and quality level
• Consistent line weight and shading approach
• Compatible with both light and dark system themes
• All sprites optimized for low-resolution displays
• Consistent file naming: [mascot]_[variant]_[size].png

TECHNICAL CONSTRAINTS:
• Total storage for all mascots: <2MB
• Support for 16-bit color (65,536 colors)
• Must be recognizable at 16x16px for system tray
• PNG format with alpha transparency
• Optimized compression without visible quality loss

EXPRESSION VARIANTS (All Mascots):
Each mascot needs the following expressions:
• Neutral/Default - Standard appearance
• Happy/Success - Task completion, positive feedback
• Thinking - Processing, waiting for input
• Concerned - Errors, warnings, attention needed
• Explaining - Tutorial mode, help dialogs

CULTURAL SENSITIVITY:
• Mythology references should be respectful and researched
• Avoid stereotypes or cultural appropriation
• Nekomata design should honor Japanese folklore traditions
• Dragon design should blend Eastern/Western traditions respectfully
• Hydra design should reference Greek mythology appropriately

